g.text: In acute myeloid leukemia blasts, p53 primarily
regulates apoptosis and cell cycle arrest. It activates
the p21 (CDKN1A) pathway to induce G1/S phase
arrest and promotes apoptosis through BAX and PUMA
upregulation. Recent studies also show that p53
directly activates the PI3K/AKT/mTOR pathway to
